'''CaÃ±ar''' or '''CaÃ±ari''' is a poorly attested [[extinct languages of the MaraÃ±Ã³n River basin|extinct language of the MaraÃ±Ã³n River basin]] in Ecuador which is difficult to classify, apart from being apparently related to [[PuruhÃ¡ language|PuruhÃ¡]], though it may have been [[Chimuan languages|Chimuan]] or [[Barbacoan languages|Barbacoan]]. (See [[CaÃ±ariâ€“PuruhÃ¡ languages]].) It was the original language of the [[CaÃ±ari|CaÃ±ari people]] before its replacement by [[Kichwa]] and later [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
